news.title: Delay in land allotment for furniture cluster in Indore jeopardises investment plans
news.para: Association of Furniture Manufacturers and Traders claimed that over 100 industrialists who have proposed to take land in the cluster have made a partial payment to Special Purpose Vehicle (SPV) formed to develop the cluster.

news.title: Soon, check status of land digitally in state: Punjab Housing Minister
news.para: Housing and urban development minister Aman Arora on Sunday directed department officials to tie-up with Punjab Remote Sensing Centre(PRSC) team to speed up this project to provide all information pertaining to land.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to come up with 340 flats instead of 492 in Sector 53
news.para: Around 100 one BHK flats will be scrapped and the number of economic weaker section (EWS) category flats reduced from 80 to 48. There will be now be 192 flats of 3 BHK, 100 of 2BHK and the remaining 48 of EWS category, according to the revised plan.

news.title: NTC forms panel for rehabilitating people living on mill land: Commerce Minister
news.para: National Textile Corporation, along with the Maharashtra government, including Mhada and MMRDA, has formed a committee to speed up the redevelopment of the land under nine of its mills in the city, Goyal told reporters without specifying which are those mills being identified.

news.title: Get nod before regularising colonies in unidentified forest area: Forest department to DDA
news.para: The Central government launched the Prime Minister-Unauthorised Colonies in Delhi Awas Adhikar Yojana (PM-UDAY) in December 2019 to give ownership rights to the residents of 1,731 unauthorised colonies in the national capital.

news.title: Now, three-storey buildings in Noida can have lifts too
news.para: Officials said residents had been approaching the Authority for several years with a request to allow lifts in buildings taller than three storeys.

news.title: Mt. K Kapital raises over Rs 350 crore as residential fund's first close from SBI, Famy Care
news.para: Around 50% of the funds raised are already in the process of being deployed towards three identified redevelopment projects in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR). The identified investment pipeline includes two projects in Mumbai’s plush Bandra locality and Andheri, with saleable areas ranging between 50,000 and 100,000 sq ft each.

news.title: MahaRERA upholds Lodha stance, allows JV to market, sell South Mumbai project
news.para: The regulator had earlier kept the registration of this project in abeyance following a plea filed by the Urban Infrastructure Venture Capital Fund (UIVCF) and had also restrained the joint entity from undertaking sales efforts.

news.title: Maharashtra to finish mapping of rural land with drones by March-end
news.para: The Union government had allocated 25 drones to the Maharashtra land records department, which comes under the settlement commissioner’s office, last year for speeding up the land survey project, which was launched to create accurate land records for rural planning and reduce property disputes.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust in dock over 'non-construction charge'
news.para: Quashing the demand for non-construction charges of Rs 1,57,000 along with incidental or consequential penalties, the District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission, Ludhiana ordered LIT to pay composite compensation of Rs 10,000 to the complainant, Harjinder Singh of Rajguru Nagar.

news.title: Call on NA tax on housing societies in February 2023: Maharashtra Revenue Minister
news.para: All properties, including housing societies, falling under the ‘gaothan’ areas, as classified by the collector in accordance with the Maharashtra Land Revenue Code, 1960, have to pay the NA tax.

news.title: Chandigarh: Sector 53 housing scheme too leaves out middle class with 'out-of-reach' pricing
news.para: The recent Supreme Court judgement freezing the floor area ratio has further raised doubts whether the government agency will be able to lower its prices for the new proposed inventory.

news.title: In land acquisition matters, even tenant needs to be heard before issuance of final declaration: Karnataka HC
news.para: On June 9,2016, a gazette notification was issued for acquisition of these land for establishment of a Rehabilitation Centre vis-a-vis a result of execution of Hippargi dam Project.

news.title: Estate office's slipup caused Rs 9.4 crore loss in Chandigarh: CAG
news.para: The UT administration had leased out government built shops (SCOs)/booths in Sector 17-E in 1960s and 1970s for a period of five years.

news.title: Delhi: MCD receives property tax of Rs 55.37 crore under SAMRIDDHI scheme
news.para: Under this scheme, property owners of authorised and regularised colonies can settle all property tax related liabilities by paying property tax of the residential properties for the current year and previous five years.
